.SH NAME
WebGLRenderingContext.clear \- WebGLRenderingContext: clear() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]WebGLRenderingContext.clear()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
WebGL API clears buffers to preset values.
.PP
The preset values can be set by \f[CR]clearColor()\f[R],
\f[CR]clearDepth()\f[R] or \f[CR]clearStencil()\f[R].
.PP
The scissor box, dithering, and buffer writemasks can affect the
\f[CR]clear()\f[R] method.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
clear(mask)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]mask\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLbitfield\f[R] bitwise OR mask that indicates the buffers to be
cleared.
Possible values are:
.RS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]gl.COLOR_BUFFER_BIT\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]gl.DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]gl.STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT\f[R]
.RE
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SS Exceptions
If \f[I]mask\f[R] is not one of the listed possible values, a
\f[CR]gl.INVALID_ENUM\f[R] error is thrown.
.SH EXAMPLES
The \f[CR]clear()\f[R] method accepts multiple values.
.IP
.EX
gl.clear(gl.DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT);
gl.clear(gl.DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT | gl.COLOR_BUFFER_BIT);
.EE
.PP
To get the current clear values, query the \f[CR]COLOR_CLEAR_VALUE\f[R],
\f[CR]DEPTH_CLEAR_VALUE\f[R], and \f[CR]STENCIL_CLEAR_VALUE\f[R]
constants.
.IP
.EX
gl.getParameter(gl.COLOR_CLEAR_VALUE);
gl.getParameter(gl.DEPTH_CLEAR_VALUE);
gl.getParameter(gl.STENCIL_CLEAR_VALUE);
.EE
